---
description: Package __init__.py re-export policy for calendar_backend layers
alwaysApply: true
---

Package re-export policy:

Small infrastructure packages (`db`, `domain`):
- Re-export every public top-level name from each submodule in `__init__.py`.
- Maintain an explicit `__all__` listing all re-exported names.
- Update `__init__.py` in the same change when adding public symbols to a submodule.
- Submodule imports remain valid; the barrel is convenience, not the only path.

`db/`:
- Re-export from `base.py` and `session.py` only.
- Do not re-export `migrations/`, `env.py`, or Alembic versions.

`domain/`:
- Re-export from `ids.py`, `enums.py`, `errors.py`, `time.py`, and `results.py`.

Large packages (`services`, `models`, `scheduling`, `deletion`, `orchestration`):
- Keep `__init__.py` empty or docstring-only unless Alembic requires model imports.
- Do not barrel-export service classes, ORM models, or scheduling implementations.
- Consumers import from the owning submodule (for example `services.task`, `models.plans`).

Never re-export:
- Underscore-prefixed names
- Test-only helpers (for example `FakeClock` in `tests/`)
- Optional heavy dependency internals at package root

Root `calendar_backend/__init__.py`:
- No deep re-exports of `db`, `domain`, `services`, or `models`.
